parse: Verb - Present Indicative Active - 3rd Person Singular
str2: Contraction for the third person singular present indicative of eneimi; impersonally, there is in or among.
No, not. Also ouk, and ouch a primary word; the absolute negative adverb; no or not.
Jewish. From Iouda; Judaean, i.e. Belonging to Jehudah.
Neither, nor, not even, and not. From ou and de; not however, i.e. Neither, nor, not even.
From Hellas; a Hellen or inhabitant of Hellas; by extension a Greek-speaking person, especially a non-Jew.
(a) (as adj.) enslaved, (b) (as noun) a (male) slave. From deo; a slave.
Neither, nor, not even, and not. From ou and de; not however, i.e. Neither, nor, not even.
Free, delivered from obligation. Probably from the alternate of erchomai; unrestrained, i.e. not a slave, or exempt.
Male. Arsen probably from airo; male.
Female. From the same as thelazo; female.
For. A primary particle; properly, assigning a reason.

parse: Personal / Possessive Pronoun - Nominative 2nd Person Plural
str2: You. The person pronoun of the second person singular; thou.

parse: Verb - Present Indicative Active - 2nd Person Plural
str2: I am, exist. The first person singular present indicative; a prolonged form of a primary and defective verb; I exist.
All, the whole, every kind of. Including all the forms of declension; apparently a primary word; all, any, every, the whole.
One. (including the neuter Hen); a primary numeral; one.
In, on, among. A primary preposition denoting position, and instrumentality, i.e. A relation of rest; 'in, ' at, on, by, etc.
Anointed One; the Messiah, the Christ. From chrio; Anointed One, i.e. The Messiah, an epithet of Jesus.
Of Hebrew origin; Jesus, the name of our Lord and two other Israelites.
